Task: Fully implement the "Environment View" content for all 13 sub-tabs using React state.
​1. Sub-Tab Navigation Logic:
​Ensure clicking the sub-tabs (Pods, Nodes, Deployments, etc.) updates a currentSubTab state.
​Use a conditional rendering block (switch/case) to display the correct component for each tab.
​2. Content for Specific Tabs (Per Hirer Docs):
​Deployments (The Key Requirement): >    - Create a "New Deployment" card.
​Implement Sequential Dropdowns: Pipeline (Select first) -> Provider (Enabled only after Pipeline) -> Repository (Enabled only after Provider).
​Add the Red Warning: If "GitHub" is selected, show "No account connected. [Link Account]".
​Pods & Nodes: >    - Build high-density tables with columns: Name, Status (Pulsing Green Dot), CPU % (Animated), Memory, and Restart.
​Use a setInterval to make CPU/RAM fluctuate (e.g., 12% to 15%) to simulate a "Live" environment.
​Firewall: >    - Implement the IP Whitelist table.
​Add the "Use My Current IP" button next to the input field as per Image 13.
​Diagnostics: >    - Create a black terminal-style box. Add a button "Run Check" that simulates a log scroll: > Verifying SSL... OK, > Checking Disk... 40GB Free.
​Autoscaler: >    - Add "Min Pods" and "Max Pods" range sliders and a "Current Load" indicator.
​3. Brand Refinement:
​Ensure all technical IDs (e.g., env-1234) and Website names are Corefinity Orange and clickable.
​Use a high-density font size (12px-14px) for tables to maintain the "Professional Tool" aesthetic.
​4. Data Persistence:
​Wrap the environment state in localStorage so the "added IPs" or "scaling settings" persist after a page refresh.
